-- Portugal’s Ongoing Closes Deal to Buy IG in Brazil, Folha Says
-- B y   H a r r y   M a u r e r
-- 2012-04-15T14:01:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/portugal-s-ongoing-closes-deal-to-buy-ig-in-brazil-folha-says.html
Portuguese investment company
Ongoing Strategy Investments SGPS SA has closed a deal to
acquire Brazilian news portal IG, Folha de S. Paulo reported,
without saying where it obtained the information.  Ongoing and Oi, which controls IG, have not completed the
final details of the contract, which should be signed tomorrow,
the newspaper said. The value of the sale wasn’t disclosed,
Folha added.  IG is the fifth-largest portal in  Brazil , with 23.5 million
unique visitors in March, the newspaper said, citing research
firm Ibope.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harry Maurer in  Rio de Janeiro  at 
 hmaurer@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
